#   DIFF-002: working-tree `be diff` routes a submodule's content diff past the pager

`be diff` (no args, working-tree) on a parent whose only changes live inside a *submodule's worktree* shows NOTHING in the pager and then dumps the sub diff to the terminal on quit. The pager (bro) gets only the parent-level diff, which is empty, so it displays "nothing!"; the submodule's full content diff is written straight to the terminal on a separate channel and appears only AFTER the pager exits (on `q`). The recursion itself works â€” the content is computed â€” it is just mis-routed past the pager. Repro in `$HOME/todo/code-abc` (the abc sub has working edits to `abc/URI.c`): `be diff` â†’ bro shows "nothing!", press `q` â†’ ~577 lines of `abc/URI.c` diff dump to the term. Non-tty proves the content is produced, not missing: `be diff > out` puts the whole 577-line abc sub diff in `out`. Probably a variant of [DIFF-001] (same diff-submodule-recursion path), but the failure here is output-channel routing, not non-recursion. See [DIFF-001], [Submodules], [CLAUDE].

##  Issues
The recursed submodule diff bypasses the parent's pager and lands on the bare terminal.

 -  `be diff` in a sub-dirty worktree: the pager (bro) receives only the parent-level diff, which is empty, so it shows "nothing!" while the real change is invisible.
 -  The submodule's content diff is emitted directly to the terminal, not into the pager pipe â€” it surfaces only after the pager is quit with `q`, looking like stray post-quit output.
 -  Non-tty proof it is mis-routed, not absent: `be diff > out 2>err` yields a ~577-line `abc/URI.c` diff in `out` â€” the sub recursion ran; only the tty/pager path drops it.
 -  Likely cause: the sub `be diff` recursion (the relay) writes to the inherited terminal fd instead of the parent's pager stdin, so the parent diff and the sub diff travel two separate channels.
 -  Secondary (track separately if distinct): `be status` reports "1165 ok" (clean) in the same worktree though the abc sub worktree is dirty â€” a dirty submodule worktree is not surfaced at the parent.

##  WIP (2026-06-16 â€” part-b DOES share the channel bug; "no results" localized)

Reanimated: the [DIFF-001] part-b `diff:?<sha>` recursion shares this exact bug,
surfaced by clicking a *submodule pin-only* commit in `be log:`.

 -  Repro: `be log:` â†’ click `cb71e65b` (the ABC-003 abc pin bump; parent diff is
    ONLY the `abc <old>..<new>` gitlink line, all content in the abc sub) â†’ bro shows
    *"be: no results"*. The diff itself is correct: plain `be diff:?cb71e65b` = 74
    lines (gitlink line + the abc `UTF8.h`/`UTF8.c` content); `be --tlv diff:?cb71e65b`
    = 6006 bytes carrying that content. So the diff CHAIN (commitâ†’.gitmodulesâ†’pinâ†’sub
    diff) is deterministic and CORRECT â€” the break is downstream, at the pager.
 -  "no results" localized to *`bro/BRO.c:2568-2574`*: on a left-click of a `U`-tagged
    nav URI, `BROForkBe` (`:2506`) runs `execlp(be,"be","--tlv",uri)` (`:2538`), drains
    the child via `bro_drain_tlv` (`:2560`), then `new_nhunks = bro_nhunks - hunks_save;
    if (new_nhunks == 0) { bro_flash(st,"be: no results"); }`. So for a sub-pin `diff:?<sha>`
    the forked child's TLV deterministically yields *ZERO renderable hunks* in bro â€”
    the sub-recursion's content crosses the TLV/pager boundary in a framing bro drops
    (same root as the working-tree case: the sub diff is on a channel the parent pager
    doesn't fold into its hunk list).
 -  CLICK-PATH MITIGATION (done, uncommitted in main wt): `be log:` rows now emit
    `commit:?<sha>` instead of `diff:?<sha>` (`graf/LOG.c:214` â†’ new `GRAFPackUriCommitSha`,
    `graf/GRAF.c`/`.h`). Commit-show always has a header hunk, so the CLICK no longer
    bottoms out to "no results". This does NOT fix the underlying bug: directly invoking
    `be diff:?<sub-pin-commit>` (or working-tree `be diff` over a sub-dirty wt) still
    renders empty in the pager â€” that is THIS ticket.

##  Blockers
None known. Localized to the `be diff` / `diff:` submodule-recursion + pager wiring â€” the same recursion [DIFF-001] part-b adds for `diff:?<sha>`; CONFIRMED part-b shares this channel bug (above). Fix once for both the working-tree `be diff` and the `diff:?<sha>` paths.

